
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-perlman-trill-smart-endnodes-04.txt'>
    <title>"TRILL Smart Endnodes", Radia Perlman, fangwei hu, Donald Eastlake, Kesava Krupakaran, Ting Liao</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-perlman-trill-smart-endnodes-04.txt</link>
    <description>This draft addresses the problem of the size and freshness of the endnode learning table in edge RBridges, by allowing endnodes to volunteer for endnode learning and encapsulation/decapsulation.  Such an endnode is known as a "smart endnode".  Only the attached RBridge can distinguish a "smart endnode" from a "normal endnode".  The smart endnode uses the nickname of the attached RBridge, so this solution does not consume extra nicknames.  The solution also enables Fine Grained Label aware endnodes.</description>
    <dc:date>2014-10-17T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
